com.habelitz.jsobjectizer.jsom.api.expression
Interface DotExpression

All Superinterfaces:
Expression, JSOM, PrimaryExpression
public interface DotExpression
extends PrimaryExpression

This PrimaryExpression type represents a chain of primary expressions separated by dots.

A DotExpression represents something like 

      anyPrimaryExpression.anySimplePrimaryTypeExpression
where anyPrimaryExpression may be a DotExpression again. The following table shows the possibilities of what concrete types anyPrimaryExpression and anySimplePrimaryTypeExpression could be.

DotExpression type anyPrimaryExpression (left primary expression) or primitive type anySimplePrimaryTypeExpression (right primary expression)
1 an object of type PrimaryExpression including the sub-types of PrimaryExpression
  • a ClassConstructorCall object that represents an inner new expression
  • an Identifier object
  • a PrimaryExpressionKeyword object.
2 a PrimitiveType object a PrimaryExpressionKeyword object set to KEYWORD_CLASS
3 a PrimaryExpressionKeyword object set to KEYWORD_VOID a PrimaryExpressionKeyword object set to KEYWORD_CLASS

This interface also defines appropriate constants for all the DotExpression types as stated by the table above.

Author:
Dieter Habelitz

getExpressions

java.util.List<Expression> getExpressions()
Returns a list containing all expressions, from the most left to the most right expression.

For instance, if this represents an expression like anyExpr1().anyExpr2.anyExpr2 this method would return a list containing these three expressions, starting with anyExpr1 and ending with anyExpr3.

Note that if this is of the dot expression type PRIMITIVE_TYPE_DOT_CLASS the PrimitiveType object will not be part of the list (because this object isn't of type expression).

Calling this method equals an getExpressions(null) call.

Returns:
A list containing all expressions, from the most left to the most right expression.
See Also:
getExpressions(List)

getExpressions

java.util.List<Expression> getExpressions(java.util.List<Expression> pList)
Returns a list containing all expressions, from the most left to the most right expression.

For instance, if this represents an expression like anyExpr1().anyExpr2.anyExpr2 this method would return a list containing these three expressions, starting with anyExpr1 and ending with anyExpr3.

Note that if this is of the dot expression type PRIMITIVE_TYPE_DOT_CLASS the PrimitiveType object will not be part of the list (because this object isn't of type expression).

Calling this method equals an getExpressions(null) call.

Parameters:
pList - If this argument isn't null the expressions will be added to this list and this list object will be returned. Otherwise a new list will be created for the result.
Returns:
A list containing all expressions, from the most left to the most right expression.

getLeftExpression

PrimaryExpression getLeftExpression()
Returns the expression from the dot's left side.

Note that for dot expressions of type PRIMITIVE_TYPE_DOT_CLASS the left side of the dot is a primitive type and this is not an expression. Therefore this method will always return null for that dot expression type.

Returns:
The expression from the dot's left side or null for dot expressions of type PRIMITIVE_TYPE_DOT_CLASS.
See Also:
getPrimitiveTypeFromLeft()
